cards.description: https://github.com/lonelyplanet/ebooks-assets/issues/43\\n\\nInfographics are coming through in a variety of ways, but almost none of them are ideal. Can we present them in a better looking, more predictable way?\\n\\nThere are infographic styles in the Understand CSS which are not being used:\\n\\n- `city-today-infographic-1`\\n- `city-today-infographic-2`\\n- `city-today-infographic-3`\\n\\n- `country-today-infographic-1`\\n- `country-today-infographic-2`\\n- `country-today-infographic-3`\\n\\nThese styles will force all images to be centred on the page. What we need to do is:\\n\\n- Drop a page break before the infographics\\n- Ensure that the infographics get their class.\\n\\nOrder in the manifest is what will come out the other end.\\n\\nThis change needs to be applied to CRMS and City

#5 [Ebooks] Porter - Downsample images for iPad/Generic
cards.description: https://github.com/lonelyplanet/ebooks-transporter/issues/5\\n\\nAmazon are changing their image specifications to be pro - high definition images.\\n\\nSo to fix this - we'll use high resolution images for the Remixer ePub which will be passed through to the Kindle.\\n\\nUnfortunately, the Amazon specifications conflict with Apple's size limit of 4.2 mega pixels.\\n\\nSo to get around this - we'll be downsampling images > 4.2 million pixels in size back to 4.2 million pixels for iPad and Generic titles.\\n\\nAlready done is the inclusion of Image Magick in Porter, so all that should be required is a new sample images task.\\n
